 The Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom on Thursday described as “laughable’’ trending speculation that suggested that he was a wizard. Ortom said this at the opening ceremony of a two-day Governor’s Retreat for Benue Government Appointees in Makurdi. The governor noted that he became a child of God after becoming a born- again Christian in 1979, adding that: “since then I have professed Jesus Christ as my Lord and Saviour’’ He, therefore, said the insinuations making around claiming he was head of wizards in Benue remained a “fallacy and laughable’’. Continue reading I am not a wizard but a born again Christian ― Ortom at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard